INSERT INTO `Directions` (RecipeID, SortOrder, Direction) VALUES ('23384', '4', 'Add the pork to the marinade, toss to coat and refrigerate for at least 3 hours.'),
('23384', '5', 'Set up the outdoor grill for direct-heat cooking over high heat. Thread the pork onto the skewers (use gloves to avoid staining your hands) and cook on the grill for 5 minutes on each side or until cooked through. Warm the naan bread briefly on the grill and serve with the tandoori pork, yogurt and cucumber.'),
('23386', '1', 'Prepare raita.'),
('23386', '2', 'Combine bulgur, tomato, and lemon juice in a small bowl.'),
('23386', '3', 'Bring broth to a boil and pour over bulgur mixture.'),
('23386', '4', 'Let stand 30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.'),
('23386', '5', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('23386', '6', 'Combine bulgur mixture, lamb, and next 6 ingredients in a medium bowl. Divide lamb mixture evenly into 6 (1/2-inchthick) patties.'),
('23386', '7', 'Place patties on a broiler pan coated with cooking spray; broil 4 to 5 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('23386', '8', 'Top bottom half of each bun with a lettuce leaf; add burgers. Spoon Feta- Cucumber Raita evenly over burgers; top with remaining half of bun.'),
('23392', '1', 'In a 2- to 2 1/2-quart pitcher, combine water, cucumber, lemon, mint, and rosemary.'),
('23392', '2', 'Serve, or cover and chill at least 2 hours or up to 8 hours.'),
('23392', '3', 'Add ice cubes just before serving.'),
('23394', '1', 'Mix the pineapple, cucumber, green onions, cilantro and mint in a large bowl.'),
('23394', '2', 'Mix the fish sauce, lime juice, sugar and chili in a small bowl.'),
('23394', '3', 'Toss the salad in the dressing to coat.'),
('23394', '4', 'Serve garnished with chopped roasted peanuts.'),
('23395', '1', 'Cook noodles as directed on package.'),
('23395', '2', 'Drain, rinse with cold water and set aside.'),
('23395', '3', 'Heat oil in a large nonstick pan over medium-high heat 1 minute. Cook garlic 30 seconds (do not brown). Reduce heat to medium.'),
('23395', '4', 'Add pork and salt; cook until browned, about 2 minutes.'),
('23395', '5', 'Add squid; sauté 1 minute. Cover. Cook until squid is opaque, about 2 minutes.'),
('23400', '1', 'Combine all ingredients, stirring well. Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add one-third of vegetable mixture. Process 30 seconds or until smooth.'),
('23400', '2', 'Transfer mixture to a bowl. Repeat procedure twice with remaining mixture. Cover and chill at least 3 hours.'),
('23408', '1', 'Heat oven to 450 F. Slice each eggplant in half lengthwise, cutting only about 3/4 of the way through so the eggplant halves remain attached at the top. Arrange the eggplants in a baking dish at least 2 inches deep, such as a 9-by-13-inch pan. Thinly slice 1 lemon. Squeeze the juice from the remaining 2 lemons. Insert the lemon slices into the slit in each eggplant, then press some garlic and oregano into each slit. Season with the salt and pepper.'),
('23408', '2', 'Drizzle the eggplants with the lemon juice and oil. Cover with foil and roast, basting frequently with the juices in the dish, until the eggplants are very soft, about 40 minutes.'),
('23408', '3', 'Remove foil and roast for 5 more minutes.'),
('23408', '4', 'Transfer to individual plates and top with the pan juices and Feta.'),
('23415', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 200°F.'),
('23415', '2', 'Cut the eggplants in half lengthways,cutting straight through the green stalk (the stalk is for thelook; don''t eat it). Use a small sharp knife to make three or fourparallel incisions in the cut side of each eggplant half, withoutcutting through to the skin. Repeat at a 45-degree angle to geta diamond-shaped pattern.'),
('23415', '3', 'Place the eggplant halves, cut-side up, on a baking sheet linedwith parchment paper.'),
('23415', '4', 'Brush them with olive oil—keep onbrushing until all of the oil has been absorbed by the flesh.Sprinkle with the lemon thyme leaves and some salt and pepper.Roast for 35 to 40 minutes, at which point the flesh should besoft, flavorful and nicely browned.'),
('23415', '5', 'Remove from the oven andallow to cool down completely.'),
('23415', '6', 'While the eggplants are in the oven, cut the pomegranate intotwo horizontally. Hold one half over a bowl, with the cut sideagainst your palm, and use the back of a wooden spoon or arolling pin to gently knock on the pomegranate skin. Continuebeating with increasing power until the seeds start coming outnaturally and falling through your fingers into the bowl. Once allare there, sift through the seeds to remove any bits of white skinor membrane.'),
('23415', '7', 'To make the sauce.'),
('23415', '8', 'Whisk together all of the ingredients. Tastefor seasoning, then keep cold until needed.'),
('23415', '9', 'To serve, spoon plenty of buttermilk sauce over the eggplanthalves without covering the stalks. Sprinkle za''atar and plenty ofpomegranate seeds on top and garnish with lemon thyme. Finishwith a drizzle of olive oil.'),
('23415', '10', 'Reprinted with permission from Plenty by Yotam Ottolenghi, (C) 2011 Chronicle Books'),
('23423', '1', 'Preheat broiler with a rack 4 in. from heat source.'),
('23423', '2', 'Heat oil in an ovenproof frying pan over high heat.'),
('23423', '3', 'Add eggplant, flesh side down, and cook until flesh starts to brown and soften, about 4 minutes.'),
('23423', '4', 'In a small bowl, combine miso, sugar, sake, and chile flakes. Turn eggplant flesh side up and brush mixture over it. Broil eggplant in pan until glaze starts to brown, about 3 minutes. Sprinkle with cilantro and sesame seeds.'),
('23423', '5', '*Look for miso, a fermented soybean paste, in the refrigerator aisle of your produce section.'),
('23433', '1', 'In a small bowl, cover the capers with warm water and let stand for 1 hour.'),
('23433', '2', 'Drain well. Meanwhile, partially peel the eggplant, leaving vertical stripes. Chop the striped eggplant into 1-inch dice.'),
('23433', '3', 'In a large skillet, heat 1 inch of vegetable oil to 35'),
('23433', '4', 'Add one-fourth of the eggplant at a time and fry over moderately high heat until golden brown, about 2 minutes.'),
('23433', '5', 'Drain on paper towels.'),
('23433', '6', 'Discard the vegetable oil and wipe out the pan. In the same saucepan, heat the olive oil.'),
('23433', '7', 'Add the sliced onions and bay leaves and cook over moderately low heat until the onions are softened but not browned, about 10 minutes.'),
('23433', '8', 'Add the capers, celery, tomatoes, olives and pine nuts and simmer, stirring a few times, until the vegetables are heated through, about 5 minutes.'),
('23433', '9', 'In a small saucepan, dissolve the sugar in the vinegar over moderate heat. Stir the vinegar mixture into the vegetables with the reserved eggplant.'),
('23433', '10', 'Transfer to a serving bowl. Season the caponatina with salt and black pepper, and let cool to room temperature.'),
('23443', '1', 'Save Recipe'),
('23443', '2', 'Print Recipe'),
('23443', '3', 'Sweet and Sour Eggplant'),
('23443', '4', 'Ingredients1 lb. Chinese or Japanese eggplants, cubed1 red bell pepper3 tbsp soy sauce2 tbsp brown sugar2 tbsp rice vinegar1 clove garlic, minced1/4 tsp cayenne (optional, adds spiciniess)2 tsp cornstarch 3 tbsp peanut oil (or another oil with a high smoke point)1 tbsp sesame seeds'),
('23443', '5', 'Salt and pepper to taste2 cups cooked long grain rice, white or brown (optional)'),
('23443', '6', 'Servings: 2'),
('23443', '7', 'Kosher Key: Pareve'),
('23444', '1', 'In a small saucepan, bring sake and mirin to a boil and boil 30 seconds. Lower heat to medium and add miso, whisking until dissolved.'),
('23444', '2', 'Add sugar and ginger and whisk until sugar dissolves.'),
('23444', '3', 'Pour half of miso mixture into a large bowl and the other half into a medium baking dish and let cool, about 10 minutes.'),
('23444', '4', 'Slice eggplant on the diagonal into 1/4-in.-thick ovals and add to miso mixture in bowl, turning to coat. Nestle salmon fillets, skin side up, into miso mixture in baking dish to coat all the flesh, but not the skin. Cover both bowl and dish with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 8 hours and up to overnight.'),
('23444', '5', 'Prepare a gas or charcoal grill for indirect heat. If using a gas grill, turn all burners to high and close lid. When the temperature inside the grill reaches 400, lift lid and turn off one of the burners, creating the indirect-heat area. If using a charcoal grill, light 50 to 60 briquets and let burn until just covered with ash, 20 to 30 minutes. Mound them to one side, leaving a cleared area for indirect cooking.'),
('23444', '6', 'Shake marinade off eggplant. Oil an unperforated sheet of heavy-duty foil with canola oil and arrange eggplant on it in 1 layer.'),
('23444', '7', 'Drizzle with 1/3 cup oil and grill over indirect heat area, 15 to 20 minutes, or until soft. Set aside.'),
('23444', '8', 'Fold two 12- by 18-in. pieces of heavy-duty aluminum foil in half widthwise to form rectangles. Using the tip of a small knife, make holes in rectangles about 2 in. apart and widen each hole to the size of a dime. Grease foil with oil; set over direct heat for 2 minutes.'),
('23444', '9', 'With paper towels, wipe marinade off salmon.'),
('23444', '10', 'Brush salmon skins with oil and set 2 fillets, skin side down, on each foil rectangle. Cover grill (if using charcoal, open vents on lid) and cook fish until skin is light brown and really sizzling, 5 to 6 minutes. Using tongs, slide foil to indirect heat, cover, and cook until all but top 1/4 in. is cooked, 3 to 8 minutes. Slide fish back over direct heat, cover, and cook until fish is cooked through (cut to test) and skin is browned and crisp, about 3 minutes. While salmon is finishing on direct heat, reheat eggplant over indirect heat.'),
('23444', '11', 'Transfer foil with salmon to a rimless baking sheet and, sliding an offset cake spatula or other thin spatula between salmon skin and foil, very gently free fish from foil. Season each fillet with a few drops of lemon juice.'),
('23444', '12', 'Serve salmon and eggplant sprinkled with chives.'),
('23447', '1', 'Salt both sides of the eggplant rounds and place in a colander for 30 to 60 minutes. Rinse. Pat each slice dry with paper towels.'),
('23447', '2', 'Brush a cookie sheet with 1 teaspoon olive oil.'),
('23447', '3', 'Place the eggplant in one layer on the sheet and brush tops with remaining 2 teaspoons olive oil.'),
('23447', '4', 'Broil rounds for 7-10 minutes until cooked through and browned. (No need to flip them.) Sprinkle on fresh salt and pepper.'),
('23447', '5', 'Whisk together miso and water.'),
('23447', '6', 'Whisk in vinegar, ginger, and lime juice.'),
('23447', '7', 'Drizzle sauce over eggplants and garnish with scallion.'),
('23450', '1', 'Place raisins in a small bowl; cover with hot water.'),
('23450', '2', 'Let stand 15 minutes; drain. Set aside.'),
('23450', '3', 'Place eggplant in a colander; sprinkle with salt. Toss well.'),
('23450', '4', 'Drain 1 hour. Rinse well; pat dry with paper towels.'),
('23450', '5', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('23450', '6', 'Add eggplant; saut 9 minutes or until well browned. Spoon eggplant into a large bowl; set aside.'),
('23450', '7', 'Heat remaining 1 teaspoon oil in pan over medium-high heat.'),
('23450', '8', 'Add onion; saut 3 minutes or until golden.'),
('23450', '9', 'Add garlic; saut 1 minute.'),
('23450', '10', 'Add tomato; saut 2 minutes.'),
('23450', '11', 'Add tomato mixture to eggplant.'),
('23450', '12', 'Return pan to heat.'),
('23450', '13', 'Add sugar and vinegar, stirring until sugar dissolves. Stir in raisins, olives, and capers.'),
('23450', '14', 'Add eggplant mixture, stirring to combine.'),
('23450', '15', 'Remove from heat; stir in parsley.'),
('23450', '16', 'Serve warm or at room temperature.'),
('23450', '17', 'Note: Caponata will keep in the refrigerator for up to 5 days; bring to room temperature before serving.'),
('23452', '1', 'Cut eggplants in half, and grill or broil over high heat 10 minutes on each side or until soft and charred on the outside, but not burned through.'),
('23452', '2', 'Scoop eggplant from skin when cool enough to handle, and combine with remaining ingredients.'),
('23452', '3', 'Serve with Moroccan flatbread or pita wedges.'),
('23453', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 35'),
('23453', '2', 'In a blender or food processor, puree the tomatoes with their juices and the 2 tablespoons of olive oil. Season the sauce with salt.'),
('23453', '3', 'Put the flour, eggs and bread crumbs in 3 large, shallow bowls. Working with 1 slice at a time, dredge the eggplant in the flour; shake off any excess. Dip the slice in the egg, letting any excess drip back into the bowl, then coat with the bread crumbs.'),
('23453', '4', 'In a large nonstick skillet, heat 1/8 inch of oil until shimmering. Line a rack with paper towels.'),
('23453', '5', 'Add one-third of the garlic and breaded eggplant to the hot oil. Cook over moderate heat, turning once and adjusting the heat as needed, until the eggplant slices are golden brown and tender, about 6 minutes.'),
('23453', '6', 'Transfer the fried eggplant to the paper towels to drain. Using a slotted spoon, discard the fried garlic. Repeat 2 more times with the remaining garlic and breaded eggplant, wiping out the skillet and adding more oil as needed.'),
('23453', '7', 'Lightly oil a 10-inch springform pan. Line the bottom with a single layer of eggplant.'),
('23453', '8', 'Spread 1/2 cup of the tomato sauce over the eggplant. Top with a few mozzarella slices and sprinkle with 3 tablespoons of the parmesan. Tear one-third of the basil leaves over the cheese. Repeat with the remaining ingredients for a total of 4 layers, ending with a layer of eggplant and a thick layer of tomato sauce. Sprinkle the remaining parmesan on top.'),
('23453', '9', 'Wrap the entire pan in foil and set it on a large rimmed baking sheet.'),
('23453', '10', 'Bake the eggplant for about 1 hour, until heated through.'),
('23453', '11', 'Increase the oven temperature to 40'),
('23453', '12', 'Remove the foil from the top of the eggplant and bake for about 10 minutes longer, until lightly browned on top.'),
('23453', '13', 'Remove from the oven and let rest for at least 15 minutes before unmolding.'),
('23453', '14', 'Cut into wedges and serve.'),
('23455', '1', 'Light a grill or preheat the broiler. In a mortar, mash the garlic with the sugar, crushed red pepper and a large pinch each of salt and pepper until a paste forms. Stir in the lime juice and cilantro.'),
('23455', '2', 'Transfer half of the mixture to a medium bowl and stir in the water, fish sauce and scallion to make a dipping sauce.'),
('23455', '3', 'Brush the eggplants with 1 1/2 tablespoons of the oil and season with salt and pepper. Season the chicken with salt and pepper. Stir the remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons of oil into the remaining garlic-lime mixture and spread it all over the chicken. Grill or broil the chicken and eggplants, turning once, until cooked through, about 5 minutes for the eggplants and 12 minutes for the chicken.'),
('23455', '4', 'Transfer to a platter and serve at once with the dipping sauce.'),
('23456', '1', 'Preheat grill to medium-high heat (350 to 400).'),
('23456', '2', 'Drizzle both sides of eggplant with olive oil, and season to taste with salt and pepper. Grill 6 minutes on each side or until tender. Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.'),
('23456', '3', 'Drizzle with additional olive oil, if desired.'),
('23461', '1', 'Heat the olive oil in a large frying pan over medium heat.'),
('23461', '2', 'Add onion and cook until soft, about 4 minutes.'),
('23461', '3', 'Add garlic and cook another minute, then add eggplant, salt, chile flakes, and pepper. Stir to coat with oil and turn heat to medium-low. Cook, stirring every few minutes, until eggplant is soft, about 20 minutes.'),
('23461', '4', 'Stir in mint.'),
('23461', '5', 'Let mixture cool to room temperature and spoon onto bruschettas.'),
('23461', '6', 'Drizzle with extra-virgin olive oil.'),
('23467', '1', 'Cut eggplant lengthwise into quarters, and cut each quarter crosswise into 4 pieces.'),
('23467', '2', 'Combine the eggplant and 1/4 teaspoon salt in a large saucepan; add water to cover, and bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 8 minutes or just until pulp can be removed from peel. Carefully remove pulp, reserving peels. Mash pulp; set aside.'),
('23467', '3', 'Heat 2 teaspoons oil in a nonstick skillet over medium heat.'),
('23467', '4', 'Add eggplant pulp and onion; saut for 7 minutes or until tender.'),
('23467', '5', 'Remove from heat; stir in breadcrumbs, 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons Romano cheese, parsley, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, and 1 minced garlic clove.'),
('23467', '6', 'Arrange reserved eggplant peels in a single layer in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray. Spoon about 2 tablespoons eggplant mixture onto each peel.'),
('23467', '7', 'Bake at 350 for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.'),
('23467', '8', 'Place a saucepan coated with cooking spray over medium heat.'),
('23467', '9', 'Add 1 minced garlic clove; saut 30 seconds.'),
('23467', '10', 'Add tomato sauce, basil, 1/8 teaspoon salt, and 1/8 teaspoon pepper, and cook 3 minutes or until heated. Spoon sauce over eggplant; sprinkle with remaining cheese, and garnish with parsley, if desired.'),
('23467', '11', 'Serve warm.'),
('23472', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 42'),
('23472', '2', 'On a work surface, mash the garlic to a paste with a pinch of salt. In a large roasting pan, mix the paste with the curry powder and vegetable oil.'),
('23472', '3', 'Add the eggplant, onion, chickpeas and ginger, season with salt and pepper and toss well.'),
('23472', '4', 'Spread the vegetables in an even layer and roast for about 30 minutes, stirring once or twice, until the eggplant and onion are tender. Stir in the spinach and roast just until wilted, about 2 minutes.'),
('23472', '5', 'Serve with warm naan and yogurt.'),
('23478', '1', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('23478', '2', 'Cut bell pepper in half lengthwise; discard seeds and membranes.'),
('23478', '3', 'Place halves, skin sides up, on foil-lined baking sheet; flatten with hand. Broil 15 minutes or until blackened.'),
('23478', '4', 'Place in a heavy-duty zip-top plastic bag; seal.'),
('23478', '5', 'Let stand 15 minutes. Peel; cut into 1/2-inch squares.'),
('23478', '6', 'Heat 1 teaspoon oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('23478', '7', 'Add eggplant; cook 6 minutes or until browned, stirring frequently.'),
('23478', '8', 'Add salt and black pepper; stir well.'),
('23478', '9', 'Remove from pan.'),
('23478', '10', 'Add 2 teaspoons oil and onion to pan; cook 3 minutes or until onion begins to brown, stirring frequently.'),
('23478', '11', 'Add garlic, thyme, and anchovy paste; cook 2 minutes, stirring frequently.'),
('23478', '12', 'Add vinegar; cook 30 seconds.'),
('23478', '13', 'Add eggplant and capers; stir well.'),
('23478', '14', 'Remove from heat.'),
('23478', '15', 'Stir in bell pepper and parsley. Cool to room temperature before serving.'),
('23478', '16', 'Serve with Polenta Crostini.'),
('23478', '17', '(Totals include Polenta Crostini)'),
('23479', '1', 'Light a grill. In a small bowl, combine the olive oil with the lemon juice, soy sauce, curry powder and crushed red pepper.'),
('23479', '2', 'Put the eggplant halves on a rimmed baking sheet, cut sides up, and coat generously with the marinade.'),
('23479', '3', 'Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes.'),
('23479', '4', 'Meanwhile, in a small bowl, mix the yogurt with the basil, cumin, garlic and lemon zest. Season the yogurt sauce with salt and pepper.'),
('23479', '5', 'Grill the eggplants, cut sides down, over a medium fire, until they are lightly charred and tender, about 4 minutes per side.'),
('23479', '6', 'Serve the grilled eggplants with the yogurt sauce.'),
('23480', '1', 'Preheat oven to 45'),
('23480', '2', 'Split eggplant in half lengthwise.'),
('23480', '3', 'Place eggplant, cut sides down, on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.'),
('23480', '4', 'Bake at 450 for 20 minutes or until eggplant is tender and cut sides are browned.'),
('23480', '5', 'Remove from oven; cool completely. Using a fork, carefully remove flesh of eggplant from skin. Discard skin; finely chop flesh, and place in a bowl.'),
('23480', '6', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('23480', '7', 'Add shallots and garlic to pan; saut 2 minutes or until tender. Stir in figs, 1/2 cup water, vinegar, 1 tablespoon juice, sugar, salt, and pepper. Simmer 5 minutes or until liquid almost evaporates.'),
('23480', '8', 'Remove from heat. Stir in remaining 1 teaspoon juice, pine nuts, and parsley.'),
('23480', '9', 'Wine Note: Oak-aged Chardonnay is tricky to pair with food, but the Eggplant and Fig Caponata is perfect with the wine''s rich flavors. The toasted nuts and figs in the dish are echoed in many barrel-aged Chardonnays, like the toasty, spicy Voyager Estate Chardonnay 2004 ($2'),
('23480', '10', 'from West Australia. This cool-climate wine also offers plenty of citrus and melon, along with bright acidity. -Jeffery Lindenmuth'),
('23483', '1', 'Preheat oven to 45'),
('23483', '2', 'Cut each eggplant into 1/4-inch slices, cutting to, but not through, stem end. Fan eggplants, and place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.'),
('23483', '3', 'Brush 1 1/2 tablespoons oil evenly over eggplant slices.'),
('23483', '4', 'Bake at 450 for 15 minutes; remove from oven. Press eggplants gently to fan slices.'),
('23483', '5', 'Brush eggplants with 1 1/2 teaspoons oil; sprinkle evenly with salt and pepper.'),
('23483', '6', 'Bake an additional 10 minutes or until flesh is tender and edges are browned and slightly crisp.'),
('23483', '7', 'Drizzle remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons oil evenly over eggplants; sprinkle with herbs.'),
('23488', '1', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('23488', '2', 'Arrange the eggplant slices on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray; broil 3 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.'),
('23488', '3', 'Preheat oven to 37'),
('23488', '4', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray over medium heat; add onion and next 4 ingredients (onion through mushrooms). Cover and cook 7 minutes or until tender, stirring mixture occasionally. Increase heat to medium-high; uncover and cook for 2 minutes or until liquid evaporates.'),
('23488', '5', 'Spread half of mushroom mixture in bottom of a 1 1/2-quart round baking dish coated with cooking spray. Arrange half of eggplant slices over mushroom mixture; sprinkle with 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Top with 1/2 cup tomato sauce and 1/3 cup mozzarella.'),
('23488', '6', 'Spread remaining mushroom mixture over mozzarella; top with remaining eggplant slices. Sprinkle with 1/8 teaspoon pepper; top with remaining tomato sauce. Cover and bake at 375 for 1 hour. Sprinkle with 1/3 cup mozzarella and Parmesan.'),
('23488', '7', 'Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until cheese melts.'),
('23488', '8', 'Let stand 10 minutes.'),
('23493', '1', 'Halve the eggplants lengthwise and cut out the flesh, leaving 1/4-inch shells.'),
('23493', '2', 'Cut the flesh into 1/2-inch dice. Salt the eggplant shells and let stand for 30 minutes. Pat the shells dry.'),
('23493', '3', 'Preheat the oven to 35'),
('23493', '4', 'Rub the eggplants with oil; set them on a rimmed baking sheet, cut side down.'),
('23493', '5', 'Add 1/4 cup of water, cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes.'),
('23493', '6', 'Meanwhile, in a skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil.'),
('23493', '7', 'Add the mushrooms. Season with salt and pepper, cover and cook over moderate heat until tender; transfer to a bowl.'),
('23493', '8', 'Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in the skillet.'),
('23493', '9', 'Add the diced eggplant. Season with salt and pepper, cover and cook until tender and browned, 3 minutes; add to the mushrooms.'),
('23493', '10', 'Add the garlic, onion and 2 tablespoons of olive oil to the skillet. Cover and cook, until softened.'),
('23493', '11', 'Add the cumin and 1 tablespoon of the butter and stir until fragrant, 1 minute; add to the mushrooms. Stir in the wine-soaked bread, cheese and broth and season the filling with salt and pepper.'),
('23493', '12', 'Increase the oven temperature to 42'),
('23493', '13', 'Turn the eggplant shells cut side up and fill with the bread stuffing. Dot the tops with the remaining 1 tablespoon of butter and bake in the upper third of the oven for 10 minutes.'),
('23493', '14', 'Preheat the broiler. Broil the eggplant 4 inches from the heat until browned, 2 minutes. Top with the parsley and serve.'),
('23496', '1', 'In a small bowl, cover the capers with water and let soak for 15 minutes; drain.'),
('23496', '2', 'Meanwhile, in a large skillet, heat 3  tablespoons of the olive oil.'),
('23496', '3', 'Add the eggplant and  cook over moderately high heat until the bottom browns, 5 minutes. Stir and cook until browned all over, 10 minutes longer.'),
('23496', '4', 'Transfer the eggplant to a bowl.'),
('23496', '5', 'Add the remaining 1 tablespoon of olive oil, the onion and celery to the skillet. Cover and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes.'),
('23496', '6', 'Add the tomato, cover and cook until soft, about 5 minutes.'),
('23496', '7', 'In a saucepan, simmer the vinegar and sugar to dissolve the sugar.'),
('23496', '8', 'Add the pine nuts and capers and cook for 1 minute.'),
('23496', '9', 'Return the eggplant to the skillet. Stir in the vinegar mixture and cook over low heat for 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper and transfer to a bowl.'),
('23496', '10', 'Let cool to room temperature, then fold in the avocado.'),
('23498', '1', 'Carefully remove pulp from each eggplant, reserving shells. Coarsely chop pulp to measure 6 cups.'),
('23498', '2', 'Place eggplant shells, cut sides down, in a 10-inch square baking dish.'),
('23498', '3', 'Add water to dish. Cover and microwave at high 5 minutes or until shells are tender. Keep warm.'),
('23498', '4', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('23498', '5', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray over medium-high heat.'),
('23498', '6', 'Add eggplant pulp; saute 7 minutes.'),
('23498', '7', 'Add onion; saut 2 minutes. Stir in tomato, wine, and garlic; cook 3 minutes or until liquid almost evaporates, stirring occasionally.'),
('23498', '8', 'Remove from heat; add feta, 1/4 cup parsley, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and pepper, stirring to combine. Spoon 3/4 cup eggplant mixture into each eggplant shell.'),
('23498', '9', 'Place the bread slices in food processor; pulse 10 times or until coarse crumbs measure 1 cup.'),
('23498', '10', 'Combine breadcrumbs, 1/4 cup parsley, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and Parmesan, stirring well. Sprinkle 1/4 cup breadcrumb mixture over each stuffed shell. Arrange shells on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray; broil 2 minutes or until lightly browned.'),
('23502', '1', 'Combine first 5 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.'),
('23502', '2', 'Heat oil in an ovenproof Dutch oven over medium-high heat.'),
('23502', '3', 'Add spice mixture, eggplant, and next 6 ingredients (eggplant through garlic); saut 3 minutes.'),
('23502', '4', 'Add tomato juice, orange juice, and water; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer 2 minutes.'),
('23502', '5', 'Remove from heat; stir in couscous. Cover and bake at 350 for 20 minutes.'),
('23504', '1', 'Prepare grill to medium heat.'),
('23504', '2', 'Cut eggplant crosswise into 8 (1/2-inch-thick) slices. Lightly coat both sides of eggplant slices with cooking spray; sprinkle with 1/8 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.'),
('23504', '3', 'Place on a grill rack coated with cooking spray; grill 7 minutes on each side or until browned. Set eggplant slices aside.'),
('23504', '4', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('23504', '5', 'Add fennel and onion; saut 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender and lightly browned.'),
('23504', '6', 'Combine remaining 1/8 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper, arugula, vinegar, and oil in a medium bowl; toss gently to coat. Divide arugula mixture evenly among 8 appetizer plates; top each serving with 1 eggplant slice. Arrange about 1/3 cup fennel mixture on each eggplant slice; top with 2 tablespoons tomatoes and 1 tablespoon cheese. Sprinkle the chopped basil and thyme evenly over cheese.'),
('23505', '1', 'Toss eggplant with 1 teaspoon salt and drain in a colander, stirring occasionally, 45 minutes.'),
('23505', '2', 'Rinse eggplant under cold water and dry well, pressing out any excess moisture.'),
('23505', '3', 'Stir together mirin, soy sauce, ginger, and seven-spice powder.'),
('23505', '4', 'Heat oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over medium-high heat until it shimmers, then sauté eggplant until browned, about 8 minutes. Stir in mirin mixture and cook, gently stirring and turning frequently, until sauce becomes a glaze and eggplant is browned and tender, about 1 minute.'),
('23505', '5', 'Serve hot or at room temperature, sprinkled with chives.'),
('23507', '1', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('23507', '2', 'Halve eggplants lengthwise.'),
('23507', '3', 'Brush cut sides with 1/4 cup oil and season with salt. Arrange as many eggplants, cut sides up, as will fit in 1 layer on rack of a broiler pan and broil 2 to 3 inches from heat until browned, about 5 minutes. Turn oven setting to 450°F. and move pan to middle of oven. Roast until tender when pierced with a fork, about 12 minutes. Repeat with remaining eggplants.'),
('23507', '4', 'Blend remaining 1 1/2 cups oil and remaining ingredients in a blender until emulsified.'),
('23507', '5', 'Serve eggplants at room temperature, drizzled with vinaigrette.'),
('23508', '1', 'If using whole-milk plain yogurt, drain in a paper-towel-lined sieve set over a bowl, covered and chilled, 8 to 12 hours.'),
('23508', '2', 'Mince garlic and mash to a paste with a pinch of salt, then transfer to a bowl.'),
('23508', '3', 'Whisk in lebneh or drained yogurt, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and enough water to make mixture resemble well-stirred sour cream.'),
('23508', '4', 'Prepare grill for cooking. If using a charcoal grill, open vents on bottom of grill, then light charcoal. Charcoal fire is medium-hot when you can hold your hand 5 inches above rack for 3 to 4 seconds. If using a gas grill, preheat burners on moderately high, covered, 10 minutes, then reduce heat to moderate.'),
('23508', '5', 'Brush eggplant slices generously with oil on both sides and sprinkle with remaining 3/4 teaspoon salt. Grill slices on lightly oiled grill rack, covered only if using a gas grill, turning over occasionally, until eggplant is tender, 12 to 15 minutes total.'),
('23508', '6', 'Transfer as cooked to a platter, arranging slices in 1 layer. Put a spoonful of yogurt mixture on each eggplant slice and top with a mint leaf.'),
('23511', '1', 'Heat a large enameled cast-iron casserole. Using a fork, prick the eggplant in a few places.'),
('23511', '2', 'Add the eggplant to the casserole, cover and cook over moderately low heat, turning once, until charred on the outside and soft within, about 40 minutes.'),
('23511', '3', 'Transfer the eggplant to a colander set in the sink. Using a sharp knife, make a lengthwise slit in the eggplant; let drain for 10 minutes. Scrape the flesh into a bowl, discarding the skin and any hard seeds; mash to a puree and transfer to a large skillet.'),
('23511', '4', 'Using the side of a large knife, mash the garlic to a coarse paste with 1 teaspoon of salt.'),
('23511', '5', 'Add the paste to the skillet along with the tomatoes, olive oil, parsley, cilantro, paprika, cumin and cayenne. Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until all the liquid has evaporated, about 10 minutes. Stir in the lemon juice and season with salt and pepper.'),
('23511', '6', 'Serve warm or at room temperature.'),
('23512', '1', 'Place eggplant in large bowl.'),
('23512', '2', 'Add 4 cups water and 2 teaspoons salt.'),
('23512', '3', 'Let soak 30 minutes.'),
('23512', '4', 'Drain well; pat eggplant dry with paper towels.'),
('23512', '5', 'Mix flour, baking powder, and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt in medium bowl.'),
('23512', '6', 'Whisk in milk and eggs.'),
('23512', '7', 'Heat enough oil to come 1/2 inch up sides of pan in heavy large skillet over medium heat. Working in batches, dip eggplant rounds in batter, then fry in oil until golden, about 30 seconds per side.'),
('23512', '8', 'Transfer to paper towels to drain.'),
('23512', '9', 'Warm honey in small saucepan over medium heat.'),
('23512', '10', 'Place eggplant rounds on platter.'),
('23512', '11', 'Drizzle with honey. Sprinkle with sesame seeds and mint; serve warm or at room temperature.'),
('23515', '1', 'Preheat oven to 450°F.'),
('23515', '2', 'Place eggplant and tomatoes on rimmed baking sheet; toss with oil and vinegar. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons oregano, salt, and pepper. Roast until eggplant is tender and golden brown, stirring occasionally, about 40 minutes.'),
('23515', '3', 'Transfer eggplant and tomatoes to platter. Sprinkle with feta and 2 teaspoons oregano and serve.'),
('23515', '4', 'Nutrition Data'),
('23518', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F.'),
('23518', '2', 'In a medium saucepan, melt the butter over low heat with the 8 rosemary sprigs. Turn the heat to the lowest setting and allow the rosemary and butter to fuse together, but do not let the butter brown.'),
('23518', '3', 'In a medium skillet, saute the garlic, shallots, and chopped rosemary together in the 1 tablespoon olive oil until the garlic and shallots become fragrant. Then add the lobster meat and gently cook for 3 to 5 minutes. Lightly season the lobster meat with salt and pepper.'),
('23518', '4', 'On a clean surface, take a piece of bacon and lay it out lengthwise. Coat the eggplant slices lightly with olive oil and barely season with salt and pepper. Put a piece of the coated eggplant on top of the bacon, perpendicularly. Put a piece of mozzarella on top of the eggplant. Scoop a generous portion of the lobster and place on top of the cheese. Put another piece of eggplant on top of the lobster and create an eggplant sandwich. Wrap the bacon around the sandwich then gently put on a cookie sheet or oven-safe dish. Repeat this process until all the lobster is used.'),
('23518', '5', 'Remove the rosemary sprigs from the butter and set them aside on a plate or clean surface.'),
('23518', '6', 'Pour the rosemary butter on top of the sandwiches until they are all saturated. Lightly season the sandwiches with salt and pepper before baking.'),
('23518', '7', 'Bake until the bacon has browned nicely, about 10 minutes.'),
('23518', '8', 'Garnish with the reserved rosemary sprigs.'),
('23518', '9', 'Serve hot.'),
('23522', '1', 'Heat oil in heavy large pot over medium-high heat.'),
('23522', '2', 'Add eggplant, bell peppers, fennel, and garlic; sauté until eggplant is tender, about 10 minutes.'),
('23522', '3', 'Add olives and raisins, then mix in tomato sauce and vinegar. Cover, reduce heat to medium-low, and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Uncover and simmer until caponata is thick and vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes longer.'),
('23522', '4', 'Mix in basil. Season caponata to taste with salt and pepper. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate.)'),
('23522', '5', 'Serve at room temperature.'),
('23525', '1', 'Grill the eggplant over a gas grill until the skin is completely charred or prick and place on a cookie sheet and bake in a preheated 450F oven for 20 minutes or until soft inside. Cool.'),
('23525', '2', 'Cut the eggplant in half lengthwise, drain off the liquid, and scoop out the pulp. Press the pulp through a food mill or pulse in a food processor equipped with a steel blade.'),
('23525', '3', 'Stir in the parsley, tahina, lemon juice, and garlic. For a thinner baba ghanouj that is whiter in color, add a little water.'),
('23525', '4', 'Season with salt and cayenne pepper to taste and garnish with additional chopped parsley.'),
('23525', '5', 'var article'),
('23525', '6', 'Type_27_data = {};'),
('23525', '7', 'article'),
('23525', '8', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0;'),
('23526', '1', 'Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('23526', '2', 'Add onion, celery, fennel, and garlic; saut 5 minutes or until tender. Stir in raisins and next 8 ingredients (through artichokes). Bring to a simmer; cook over medium-low heat 5 minutes or until liquid almost evaporates. Sprinkle with parsley.'),
('23526', '3', 'Serve chilled or at room temperature.'),
('23536', '1', 'Cut top and bottom off each eggplant. Peel each eggplant lengthwise with a vegetable peeler, leaving long purple stripes.'),
('23536', '2', 'Cut eggplants crosswise into 1-inch-thick slices.'),
('23536', '3', 'Line a large baking sheet with paper towels; sprinkle 1 tablespoon salt evenly over paper towels.'),
('23536', '4', 'Place eggplant slices on salt-covered paper towels. Sprinkle remaining 2 tablespoons salt over eggplant slices.'),
('23536', '5', 'Let stand 15 minutes.'),
('23536', '6', 'Remove eggplants to a colander, rinse well, and pat dry with paper towels.'),
('23536', '7', 'Place eggplants on a clean baking sheet, drizzle evenly with olive oil, and sprinkle with pepper.'),
('23536', '8', 'Bake at 425 for 20 minutes or until eggplant slices are very tender but still holding their shape.'),
('23536', '9', 'Serve with Fresh Tomato and Pomegranate Sauce.'),
('23536', '10', 'Garnish, if desired.'),
('23537', '1', 'Heat the olive oil to 365F in a large deep skillet. Beat the eggs in a wide shallow bowl.'),
('23537', '2', 'Put the bread crumbs in another shallow bowl. Working in batches, dip the eggplant in the eggs and then in the bread crumbs, turning to coat, and add to the hot oil, without crowding. Fry until golden brown, about 5 minutes.'),
('23537', '3', 'Drain on paper towels, sprinkle with salt, and serve.'),
('23538', '1', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('23538', '2', 'Pierce eggplant several times with a fork; place on a foil-lined baking sheet. Broil 30 minutes or until blackened, turning frequently. Cool eggplant slightly; peel and chop.'),
('23538', '3', 'Cut bell pepper in half lengthwise; discard seeds and membranes.'),
('23538', '4', 'Place pepper halves, skin sides up, on a foil-lined baking sheet; flatten with hand. Broil 15 minutes or until blackened.'),
('23538', '5', 'Place in a zip-top plastic bag; seal.'),
('23538', '6', 'Let stand 15 minutes. Peel and chop.'),
('23538', '7', 'Combine eggplant, bell pepper, onion, and remaining ingredients in a medium bowl; toss well.'),
('23540', '1', 'In a colander, sprinkle the eggplant with 1 teaspoon of salt and toss; let stand for 30 minutes. Squeeze out any excess water.'),
('23540', '2', 'Meanwhile, in a small bowl, soak the raisins in hot water until softened and plump, about 10 minutes.'),
('23540', '3', 'Drain.'),
('23540', '4', 'In a medium saucepan, heat 1 1/2 tablespoons of the olive oil.'),
('23540', '5', 'Add the onion and celery, cover and cook over moderately low heat until softened, about 4 minutes.'),
('23540', '6', 'Add the red bell pepper, garlic and jalapeo and cook over moderate heat until softened, about 4 minutes.'),
('23540', '7', 'Add the tomato paste and cook, stirring, until shiny, about 1 minute.'),
('23540', '8', 'Add the tomato and cook over moderately high heat, stirring a few times, until it begins to break down, about 2 minutes.'),
('23540', '9', 'Transfer the mixture to a bowl.'),
('23540', '10', 'In a large nonstick skillet, heat the remaining 1 tablespoon of olive oil until shimmering.'),
('23540', '11', 'Add the drained eggplant and cook over moderately high heat, stirring occasionally, until browned all over, about 4 minutes. Reduce the heat to moderate and cook, stirring occasionally, until the eggplant is very tender, about 3 minutes longer.'),
('23540', '12', 'Transfer the eggplant to the bowl and add the olives, capers, raisins and sherry vinegar. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('23540', '13', 'Let the caponata cool to room temperature and serve with the baguette toasts.'),
('23544', '1', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('23544', '2', 'Combine first 6 ingredients, stirring with a whisk. Arrange eggplant slices on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.'),
('23544', '3', 'Spread mirin mixture evenly over the eggplant slices, and sprinkle with sesame seeds. Broil 8 minutes or until topping is golden.'),
('23544', '4', 'Place eggplant slices on a platter, and sprinkle with onions.'),
('23546', '1', 'Preheat oven to 40'),
('23546', '2', 'Score cut side of each eggplant half by making 4 crosswise cuts.'),
('23546', '3', 'Place the eggplant halves, cut sides down, on a foil-lined baking sheet coated with cooking spray.'),
('23546', '4', 'Bake at 400 for 25 minutes or until tender.'),
('23546', '5', 'Remove from oven; cool on pan 10 minutes. Carefully remove pulp, leaving a 1/3-inch-thick shell; reserve eggplant shells. Chop pulp.'),
('23546', '6', 'Reduce oven temperature to 35'),
('23546', '7', 'Place bread in a food processor; pulse 10 times or until coarse crumbs measure 1/2 cup.'),
('23546', '8', 'Drizzle the breadcrumbs with olive oil, and pulse to combine.'),
('23546', '9', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray over medium-high heat.'),
('23546', '10', 'Add onion; saut 3 minutes. Stir in the chopped eggplant, bell pepper, tomato, oregano, and garlic; cover, reduce heat, and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Uncover and cook 5 minutes or until liquid evaporates, stirring occasionally.'),
('23546', '11', 'Remove from heat; stir in cheese, parsley, salt, and black pepper. Stuff each eggplant shell with about 1/2 cup onion mixture; sprinkle with breadcrumb mixture.'),
('23546', '12', 'Place on a baking sheet; bake at 350 for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated and lightly browned.'),
('23548', '1', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('23548', '2', 'Whisk together shiro miso, vinegar, water, sugar, and ginger until sugar is dissolved.'),
('23548', '3', 'Brush a large shallow baking pan with oil and arrange eggplant, cut sides up, in pan.'),
('23548', '4', 'Brush tops with 2 tablespoons oil (total). Broil eggplant 4 to 6 inches from heat until it begins to turn pale golden and soften, 4 to 5 minutes.'),
('23548', '5', 'Brush generously with miso mixture and broil  2 minutes more.'),
('23548', '6', 'Brush eggplant with miso again and rotate pan 180 degrees (do not turn eggplant over), then continue to broil until eggplant is tender and glaze is golden brown, 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('23548', '7', 'Serve sprinkled with scallions.'),
('23548', '8', '*Available at Asian markets, specialty foods shops, and Uwajimaya (800-889-1928).'),
('23551', '1', 'Bring a large pot of water to boil.'),
('23551', '2', 'Slice the eggplants in half lengthwise.  And then cut those pieces in half crosswise.'),
('23551', '3', 'When ready, set a steamer basket or some device above the boiling water.  Toss in the eggplants and cook until very tender, about 10 minutes.'),
('23551', '4', 'While that’s cooking, heat the oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.  Toss in the garlic and cook 4 minutes or until golden brown.'),
('23551', '5', 'Remove the garlic to a large bowl.'),
('23551', '6', 'Add the scallion, chili paste, sugar, soy sauce, sesame oil, rice vinegar, and vermouth to the large bowl.'),
('23551', '7', 'Mix until combined.'),
('23551', '8', 'When the eggplant is done, toss in the large bowl and gently toss together.'),
('23551', '9', 'Serve while warm.'),
('23552', '1', 'In a heatproof glass bowl, combine the water and sugar and microwave at high power for 10 seconds, until the sugar is dissolved.'),
('23552', '2', 'Add the grated ginger, vinegar, sesame oil and the 1/2 cup of vegetable oil and season with salt.'),
('23552', '3', 'Set a large steamer basket in a large saucepan, add 1/2 inch of water and bring to a boil over moderately high heat. Steam the eggplant in batches, cut side down, until just tender, about 4 minutes.'),
('23552', '4', 'Heat a grill pan. Lightly brush the eggplant all over with vegetable oil. Grill over high heat until grill marks appear, about 30 seconds per side, then transfer to a serving platter. Spoon the ginger sauce over the eggplant.'),
('23552', '5', 'Garnish with the purple basil (if using) and serve at once.'),
('23553', '1', 'Heat 2 tablespoons of the oil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat.'),
('23553', '2', 'Add the celery and cook, 3 minutes. Stir in the eggplant and tomatoes.In a small bowl, combine the tomato paste, vinegar, 1/4 cup water, 2 1/2 teaspoons salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, and the sugar. Stir into the eggplant. Cover and reduce heat to medium-low. Cook, stirring occasionally, until the eggplant is tender, 15 to 20 minutes.'),
('23553', '3', 'Remove from heat and stir in the capers, pine nuts (if using), and parsley.Meanwhile, cook the penne according to the package directions. Toss with the remaining oil, let cool, and cover.'),
('23553', '4', 'Combine the eggplant with the pasta before serving.'),
('23555', '1', 'Heat 3 tablespoon oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over medium heat until it shimmers, then cook eggplant with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper, stirring occasionally, until browned, about 5 minutes.'),
('23555', '2', 'Stir together tomato paste, sugar, water, and vinegar and add to eggplant with 1/3 cup scallions, then braise, covered, over medium heat until eggplant is tender, about 12 minutes.'),
('23555', '3', 'While eggplant braises, gently mix veal, dill, remaining 1/3 cup scallions, 3/4 teaspoon salt, and 1/2 teaspoon pepper in a large bowl, then form into 4 (4-inch) cakes.'),
('23555', '4', 'Heat remaining 3 tablespoons oil in a 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat until hot. Dredge veal cakes in flour, shaking off excess, then fry, turning once, until golden-brown, 8 to 12 minutes total for medium. 3Divide eggplant among 4 plates and top with veal cakes.'),
('23558', '1', 'Preheat the grill or broiler. Mound the flour and salt in the center of a cutting board. Using a pastry cutter, cut the butter into the flour until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.'),
('23558', '2', 'Mix in the egg and cold water and work the dough just enough so that it comes together. Wrap in plastic and refrigerate 30 minutes.'),
('23558', '3', 'Brush the eggplant slices with olive oil and grill on both sides until marked and crispy, about 3 minutes per side. Set aside. Meanwhile, in a 12 to 14-inch skillet, heat the olive oil over high heat until just smoking.'),
('23558', '4', 'Add the garlic and onion and saute over high heat until light golden brown.'),
('23558', '5', 'Add the mint, thyme, oregano and salt and pepper to taste and cook 5 minutes more. Stir in the tomato puree, bring to a boil, simmer until very thick and stew like and remove from heat.'),
('23558', '6', 'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.'),
('23558', '7', 'Roll the dough out to an even 1/8-inch thickness and fit it into a 10-inch tart pan. Blind bake the pastry shell for 20 minutes, until golden brown, then remove from oven and allow to cool. Layer the eggplant slices and tomato sauce mixture in the tart shell, alternating layers and ending with a layer of eggplant.'),
('23558', '8', 'Cut the slices if necessary to fit the pie shell. Top with abundant grated cheese and bake in the oven 20 minutes, until the cheese is browned and the sauce is bubbling.'),
('23558', '9', 'Let cool 15 minutes, then slice and serve.'),
('23559', '1', 'Cut the eggplants in half lengthwise and then into -inch slices.'),
('23559', '2', 'Brush them generously with oil, sprinkle lightly with salt, and cook them under the broiler for 15 minutes, or on an oiled griddle, turning them over once. They do not need to be cooked through as they will be stewed further in the sauce.'),
('23559', '3', 'In a large saucepan, heat the garlic in 1 tablespoon olive oil for seconds only, stirring, until it just begins to color.'),
('23559', '4', 'Add the tomatoes and squash them gently in the pan.'),
('23559', '5', 'Add the sugar, salt, and black pepper and cook for 15 minutes.'),
('23559', '6', 'Add the pomegranate molasses, put in the eggplants and chickpeas, and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, or until the eggplants are very soft.'),
('23559', '7', 'Serve sprinkled with chopped parsley.'),
('23559', '8', 'var article'),
('23559', '9', 'Type_27_data = {};'),
('23559', '10', 'article'),
('23559', '11', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0;'),
('23570', '1', 'Cut the eggplant into -inch-thick slices; salt them if large and time allows. Preheat the oven to 200F. Set out the flour, bread crumbs, and beaten eggs on plates or shallow bowls next to each other on your counter and have a stack of parchment or wax paper ready. Season the eggs liberally with salt and pepper.'),
('23570', '2', 'Rinse and dry the eggplant. Dredge the slices, one at a time, in the flour, then dip in the egg, then dredge in the bread crumbs. Stack the breaded cutlets between layers of wax paper and then transfer the stack to chill in the refrigerator for at least 10 minutes and up to 3 hours.'),
('23570', '3', 'Put the oil and/or butter in a deep pan on the stove and turn the heat to medium-high; when the oil, is readyabout 350Fa pinch of flour will sizzle in it. Put in a few of the eggplant slices; cook in batches as necessary, being sure not to crowd the pan, adding additional oil to the pan as necessary.'),
('23570', '4', 'Turn the eggplant slices as soon as theyre browned, then cook the other side. The total cooking time should be 5 minutes or less. As each piece is done, transfer it first to paper towels to drain briefly, then to an ovenproof platter, and transfer the platter to the oven.'),
('23570', '5', 'Serve as soon as all the pieces are cooked, garnished with the parsley, with the lemon wedges on the side.Celery Root Schnitzel.'),
('23570', '6', 'The history of vegetarianism in central Europe led to the mainstreaming of this dish, which is terrific: Substitute celery root (or potato, beet, or rutabaga) for the eggplant, cutting it into -inch-thick slices and cooking for about 10 minutes total. Proceed with the recipe.Sesame-Fried Eggplant.'),
('23570', '7', 'An Asian-style variation, thats, great with any soy-based dipping sauce : Use 2 cups of bread crumbs and 1 cup of sesame seeds for the final dredging. Replace some of the oil or butter (2 to 3 tablespoons) with sesame oil.Coconut-Fried Plantains.'),
('23570', '8', 'A totally tropical appetizer, side dish, or dessert: Substitute 4 or 5 yellow to yellow-black plantains for the eggplant; peel and cut straight or diagonal into about -inch:-thick slices. Use 1 cups bread crumbs and 1 cups shredded coconut for the final dredging.Grain-Fried Butternut Squash.'),
('23570', '9', 'Replacing part or all of the bread crumbs with ground grains adds a nutty flavor: Substitute about 2 pounds peeled and sliced butternut squash for the eggplant. Use 3 cups ground oats or barley instead of the bread crumbs for the final dredging.Fried Onion Rings, Streamlined.'),
('23570', '10', 'A simple coating of flour makes for a slightly less crunchy and really simple onion ring; these make a fantastic garnish too: Substitute 2 thinly sliced onions for the eggplant. Omit the bread crumbs and eggs; dredge the onion rings in just flour and fry until golden brown.'),
('23570', '11', 'var article'),
('23570', '12', 'Type_27_data = {};'),
('23570', '13', 'article'),
('23570', '14', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0;'),
('23571', '1', 'In a small skillet, toast the pine nuts over moderate heat, shaking the skillet frequently, until golden, about 5 minutes.'),
('23571', '2', 'Transfer to a plate and let cool.'),
('23571', '3', 'In a small saucepan, combine the vinegar and sugar and boil, then cook over high heat until reduced by half, about 6 minutes.'),
('23571', '4', 'Let cool.'),
('23571', '5', 'Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan.'),
('23571', '6', 'Add the onions and celery and cook over moderate heat until slightly softened, about 5 minutes. Stir in the eggplants and cook for 5 minutes.'),
('23571', '7', 'Add the red and yellow bell peppers and cook for 3 minutes, then stir in the zucchini and tomatoes and cook for 3 minutes longer. Gradually stir in the reduced vinegar; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring often, until the vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes. Stir in the capers, olives, pine nuts and basil. Season with salt and pepper and serve.'),
('23572', '1', 'Toss eggplant with 1 teaspoon salt in a colander set over a bowl, then let drain 30 minutes. Rinse eggplant, then drain, pressing gently on eggplant to extract any excess liquid. Pat dry.'),
('23572', '2', 'Whisk together vinegar, sugar, and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt in a small bowl until sugar is dissolved. Stir in garlic and mint.'),
('23572', '3', 'Heat oil in a 12-inch nonstick skillet over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then fry eggplant, about 8 slices at a time, until cooked through and pale golden, about 1 minute per side.'),
('23572', '4', 'Transfer eggplant as fried to paper towels to drain, then transfer to a large shallow dish, overlapping slices slightly. Spoon some of vinegar mint mixture over each batch. Marinate eggplant, covered and chilled, at least 8 hours.'),
('23575', '1', 'Preheat oven to 42'),
('23575', '2', 'Score cut side of each eggplant half in a crisscross pattern; lightly coat cut sides of eggplant halves with cooking spray.'),
('23575', '3', 'Place eggplant halves, cut sides down, on a baking sheet.'),
('23575', '4', 'Bake at 425 for 10 minutes. Turn eggplant halves over; bake an additional 10 minutes or until tender.'),
('23575', '5', 'Remove from oven; cool 10 minutes.'),
('23575', '6', 'Remove pulp from eggplant, leaving a (1/4-inch-thick) shell.'),
('23575', '7', 'Place eggplant shells on baking sheet coated with cooking spray. Chop pulp; set aside.'),
('23575', '8', 'Reduce oven temperature to 35'),
('23575', '9', 'Heat olive oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('23575', '10', 'Add ham, 1/2 cup onion, bell pepper, and garlic; saut 5 minutes.'),
('23575', '11', 'Add reserved eggplant pulp and beer; cook 10 minutes or until most of liquid evaporates, stirring occasionally. Stir in shrimp; cook 1 minute.'),
('23575', '12', 'Remove from heat.'),
('23575', '13', 'Place bread in a food processor; process until coarse crumbs form.'),
('23575', '14', 'Add breadcrumbs, 3 tablespoons cheese, green onions, basil, tarragon, rind, salt, and black pepper to eggplant mixture; stir gently to combine. Mound about 1/2 cup shrimp mixture into each eggplant shell. Sprinkle each with 1 1/2 teaspoons cheese.'),
('23575', '15', 'Bake at 350 for 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated and shrimp are done.'),
('23576', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 425°F.'),
('23576', '2', 'Halve the eggplants lengthwise.'),
('23576', '3', 'Brush the flesh lightly with 1 tablespoon of the oil and season with salt.'),
('23576', '4', 'Place the eggplant halves cut side down on a baking sheet.'),
('23576', '5', 'Place on a rack in the center of the oven and bake until soft and golden, about 30 minutes. After removing the eggplant halves from the oven, cut them in half again.'),
('23576', '6', 'While the eggplant cooks, prepare the sauce: In a large deep frying pan, combine the onion, the remaining 2 tablespoons oil, and about 1/2 teaspoon kosher salt. Toss to thoroughly coat the onions with the oil and cook, covered, over low heat until soft and translucent, about 10 minutes.'),
('23576', '7', 'Add the ginger, garlic, chile, and cumin and toss again to evenly coat the onions with the spices.'),
('23576', '8', 'Add the tomato sauce and chicken stock and simmer, covered, for about 5 minutes.'),
('23576', '9', 'Add the roasted eggplant halves, burying them in the sauce. Cook until the eggplant is very tender and has absorbed the sauce, about 20 minutes more.'),
('23578', '1', 'Pour enough oil into heavy large skillet to coat bottom; heat over medium heat.'),
('23578', '2', 'Add eggplant to skillet, arranging in single layer. Sprinkle eggplant with salt and pepper. Sauté until cooked through, but not browned, about 3 minutes per side.'),
('23578', '3', 'Transfer eggplant to sheet of foil; reserve skillet.'),
('23578', '4', 'Arrange 1 bell pepper strip atop rounded edge of each eggplant piece, trimming to fit, if necessary. Sprinkle cheese atop eggplant. do ahead Can be made 2 hours ahead.'),
('23578', '5', 'Let stand at room temperature.'),
('23578', '6', 'Arrange lettuce leaves on platter. Reheat oil in skillet over medium heat.'),
('23578', '7', 'Place eggplant, cheese side up, into skillet. Cover and cook until cheese softens and begins to melt, about 4 minutes.'),
('23578', '8', 'Place 1 eggplant piece atop each lettuce leaf. Sprinkle each with olives and oregano.'),
('23582', '1', 'In a heatproof glass bowl, combine the water and sugar and microwave at high power for 10 seconds, until the sugar is dissolved.'),
('23582', '2', 'Add the grated ginger, vinegar, sesame oil and the 1/2 cup of vegetable oil and season with salt.'),
('23582', '3', 'Set a large steamer basket in a large saucepan, add 1/2 inch of water and bring to a boil over moderately high heat. Steam the eggplant in batches, cut side down, until just tender, about 4 minutes.'),
('23582', '4', 'Heat a grill pan. Lightly brush the eggplant all over with vegetable oil. Grill over high heat until grill marks appear, about 30 seconds per side, then transfer to a serving platter. Spoon the ginger sauce over the eggplant.'),
('23582', '5', 'Garnish with the purple basil (if using) and serve at once.'),
('23585', '1', 'Place the sliced eggplant in a shallow pan with the buttermilk and marinate for 20 minutes.'),
('23585', '2', 'Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.'),
('23585', '3', 'Heat the oil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat to 350 degrees F.'),
('23585', '4', 'Beat the eggs and milk together to make an egg wash. Once the oil is to temperature, dredge the eggplant in the flour, tap off any excess, and then coat with the prepared egg wash. Slip gently into the oil and fry until golden brown, about 2 minutes. Flip and continue to cook the other side until golden brown, 2 to 3 minutes. After frying, remove to paper towels to drain. Repeat the process until all the eggplant has been fried.'),
('23585', '5', 'Lay the eggplant flat and apply about 1 tablespoon goat cheese to the bottom short edge of the eggplant. Top the goat cheese with 1 basil leaf and roll the eggplant from bottom to top, ensuring the goat cheese and basil stays in the middle of the roll.'),
('23585', '6', 'Place the rolls in a baking dish.'),
('23585', '7', 'Top the rolls with Marinara Sauce, sprinkle with Parmesan, and bake until the cheese has melted, about 10 minutes.'),
('23585', '8', 'In a saucepan over medium-high heat, add the oil and heat to the verge of smoking.'),
('23585', '9', 'Add the onions and celery and cook until the onions are translucent. Deglaze the pan with the wine, stir and scrape up any bits, and then add the red sauce and garlic. Reduce the heat and simmer for 20 minutes.'),
('23585', '10', 'Add the Worcestershire sauce, thyme, oregano, basil, and tomatoes. Season with salt and pepper. Reduce the heat and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.'),
('23586', '1', 'Using a whisk, combine the soy sauce, honey, sesame oil, sherry, ginger, and crushed red pepper.'),
('23586', '2', 'Light a charcoal grill and allow the coals to burn until covered with gray ash or heat a gas grill to medium.'),
('23586', '3', 'Brush the cut sides of the eggplant wedges with the marinade and place on grill. Grill 5 minutes.'),
('23586', '4', 'Brush the romaine and tomatoes and place on grill. Baste the eggplant and turn and cook until all the vegetables are fork-tender, about 10 minutes more.'),
